# Category
Category app is an application that allows users to record and share things they want to achieve or experience before reaching a certain age meeting the needs of keeping track of their dreams and goals.

## Group Authentication

## Registration [/auth/register]

### Register a User  [POST]

It takes a JSON object containing a username, email and password.

Password cannot be less that  characters.

Username must be Unique.


+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "username": "Bruno",
            "email" : "silverjimmy2@gmail.com",
            "password": "12345678923"

        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content-Type:application/json

    + Body

        {
            "message": "User Registration success!"
        }

## Login [/auth/login]

### Authenitcate and Authorize a user [POST]

Use your correct email and password.
Note the token returned on successful login. It is required to access other
resources.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "username": "Bruno",
            "password": "12345678923"

        }

+ Response 200

    + Headers

            Content-Type:application/json

    + Body

        {
                "status": "success",
                "message": "You have successfully logged in.",
                "auth_token": "Your_Token_Here"
        }

### Group Category

## Category endpoints [/category/]

### Create a new category  [POST]

It takes a JSON object containing a name and description.

Category name must be Unique.


+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content-Type:application/json
    + body
        {
          "name": "SouthAfrica",
          "description": "sarah@gmsil.com"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization : "Your_token_here"

    + Body

    {
        "message": "Category SouthAfrica Added!",
        "status": "success"
    }

+ Response 409 (application/json)


    + Body

        {
            "message": "This Category already exists !",
            "status": "fail"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)


    + Body

    {
        "message": "Please enter a Category name!",
        "status": "fail"
    }



